snippet.textDisplay:
At first this looked like it wasn't even intentional but she really does deliberately move her hand away. That nervous hand folding was her not knowing to do with her hands to make it seem natural.



This is really not the time for petty political squabbles. We can arguably (and truthfully) say that the fate of the planet will be decided in 2020. I really had hoped that a united front between two progressive front runners was going to be what would set this election apart from 2016, but it looks so far like the Dems are still incapable of learning from their mistakes. All that's left now is to split the vote with a bunch of negative campaigning, get Biden nominated, and watch him word salad his way into 4 more years of Trump.
The only way out of this that I can see is Warren pivoting because this doesn't play well or Bernie manages to shrug it off, keeps the momentum he has right now through Iowa, and pulls far enough ahead to make up the difference for Warren's primary base. That is, assuming the DNC doesn't screw Bernie out of a rightful nomination again.
